The First Class traditional ruler of Mbula Kingdom in Adamawa, Chief Joel Joram-Fwa, is dead. The acting Murum Mbula, Mr Fenny Fwa confirmed the monarch’s death. Fwa told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) that Joram-Fwa, died on Sunday, at the Federal Medical Centre, Yola, at the age of 82, after a brief illness. READ ALSO: DSS operatives clash with Sunday Igboho’s supporters in Ataoja’s palace He said the late Joram-Fwa is survived by a wife and 10 Children Before his death, he was a member of the Adamawa council of traditional rulers